reviews.summary:
This paper does not propose a new RNA foundation model, but systematically studies the transfer learning mechanism of existing RNA foundation models. On several structural and functional tasks, the author makes a unified evaluation of various existing encoder-only RNA Transformer, and compares the four settings of Onehot, Frozen, RI-T and PT-FT. The main conclusions of this paper are as follows: 

1) The validity of freezing representation is highly dependent on the task; 
2) Hierarchical feature reuse in similar vision is not universally established in RNA model; 
3) The benefits of pre-training are often more like providing better optimization initialization than directly providing a general representation of freezable reuse. On the whole, this is a mechanism analysis /benchmark paper.
